</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="22" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="22">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="22">
In addition to the type species, this genus includes a new congener described below. The differences are depicted in Fig. 1 and Figs 38, 40, 41, being also mentioned in the diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName class="Diplopoda" family="Opisotretidae" genus="Carlotretus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carlotretus triramus" order="Polydesmida" pageId="9" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triramus">Carlotretus triramus</taxonomicName>
sp. n.
</paragraph>
